This paper deals with object localization in medical images, which is a common task in computer vision. The proposed technique involves learning with limited annotation, which is a topic of interest in machine learning. The paper also introduces a novel loss function and a new architecture, which are relevant to the fields of deep learning and neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
